content:
I had no idea that my friends were planning a surprise party! They did an amazing job of keeping it a secret, and I was completely caught off guard when I walked into the room and saw all those familiar faces. It was a really special moment, and I'll always treasure the memory.

As for turning 30, I'd be lying if I said I wasn't a bit anxious about it. There was a part of me that felt like I was saying goodbye to my carefree twenties and entering a more serious, adult phase of life. But at the same time, I was also feeling really proud of all that I'd accomplished, and I was excited to see what the future held.

Now that I'm a few months into my thirties, I can say that it's been a really positive experience so far. I feel more confident and self-assured than ever before, and I'm loving the sense of direction and purpose that comes with getting older.
